en_4137514_1	The Prisons Commissioner General, T.M.J.W.Tennakoon had decided to take this measure due to the tension brewing up in the Negombo prison.
en_4137514_2	75 inmates have been transferred to the Anuradhapura prison, while the remainder have been transferred to the Wariyapola and Mahara prisons.
en_4137514_3	The Commissioner General went on to note that the Defence Secretary has requested to provide additional security to 11 prisons including Welikada, Magazine, Negombo, Galle and Kalutara prisons.
en_4137514_4	He noted that this request was made as the prisons held the Muslim detainees, as well as the other suspects who are arrested in the current islandwide operations.
